Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.09,0:02:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,First question.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.47,0:02:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a graduate student, and he's studying neurofeedback,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.30,0:02:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and he wants to know what does it calibrate at.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.59,0:02:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Neurofeedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.65,0:02:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Neurofeedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.81,0:02:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Neurofeedback with what?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.81,0:02:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Please explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.24,0:02:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Neurofeedback with what?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.25,0:02:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What is neurofeedback?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.65,0:02:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.31,0:02:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask about this, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.08,0:02:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We can calibrate the neurofeedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.28,0:03:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over 440, 460, 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.44,0:03:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,450 is my guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.83,0:03:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.87,0:03:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,450.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.46,0:03:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,After you do this many, many times,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.33,0:03:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to almost intuit what the number is going to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.22,0:03:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You get like a feeling for it, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.65,0:03:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.65,0:03:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's science.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.99,0:03:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Science is in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.74,0:03:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a Newtonian paradigm of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.09,0:03:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.11,0:03:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll read this question in Korean so other Koreans can understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.61,0:03:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.81,0:03:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus died on the cross to redeem all human sins,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.81,0:03:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,as the Church says.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.18,0:03:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's true,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.06,0:04:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,did all of you here, including me,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.31,0:04:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,suffer the same sin?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.55,0:04:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We are told in Korean,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.83,0:04:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Christian theology,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.90,0:04:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that the meaning of Jesus Christ's crucifixion on the cross,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.71,0:04:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the purpose of that was to redeem ourselves from our sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.52,0:04:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.35,0:04:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And if that is so,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.49,0:04:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,through that sacrifice,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.08,0:04:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ's sacrifice,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.11,0:04:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,are we all redeemed?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.12,0:04:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who believe on his name are redeemed by his sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.43,0:04:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, he was,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.25,0:04:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,incarnate, incarnate.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.07,0:04:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who believe on Jesus Christ are redeemed by Jesus Christ's sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.89,0:05:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Incarnate means that his divinity was a direct gift from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.72,0:05:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ was incarnate as a direct gift from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.08,0:05:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.67,0:05:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Jesus Christ's divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.64,0:05:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,was like a spark,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.44,0:05:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. So, Jesus Christ's divinity was like a spark,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.61,0:05:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,a special recognition from God,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.16,0:05:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jesus would serve a certain purpose for mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.16,0:05:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to redeem mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.16,0:05:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.22,0:05:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ's incarnation,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.22,0:05:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,was a direct gift from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.22,0:05:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.22,0:05:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a gift from God to save mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.56,0:05:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.56,0:06:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the biblical story is that man fell from grace
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.24,0:06:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,by disobeying God's laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.24,0:06:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And by Jesus Christ's sacrifice,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.63,0:06:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,man redeemed himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.41,0:06:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,became redeemed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.94,0:06:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So that all who believe on his name,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.51,0:06:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,or acknowledge his divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.51,0:06:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,are thereby also redeemed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.80,0:06:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.37,0:06:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.69,0:06:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it says that man fell from grace
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.69,0:06:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,by disobeying God's laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.69,0:06:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.69,0:06:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's a historical fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.69,0:06:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that man fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.69,0:06:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a biblical,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.69,0:06:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.69,0:06:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it says,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.69,0:06:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,man fell from innocence and grace
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.04,0:06:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,by disobeying God.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.24,0:06:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in the Scripture.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.24,0:06:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's in the Scripture.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.24,0:06:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.24,0:06:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It says,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.24,0:07:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,man fell from innocence and grace
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.62,0:07:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,by disobeying God.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.87,0:07:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's in the Scripture, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.87,0:07:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And by Christ's sacrifice,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.49,0:07:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,he redeemed mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.49,0:07:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, those who believe in Christ,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.51,0:07:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus is their advocate,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.95,0:07:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,advocate before the Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.95,0:07:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.72,0:07:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I will,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.72,0:07:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I will plead for you before God.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.00,0:08:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.60,0:08:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I will plead for you before God.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.70,0:08:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.70,0:08:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I will plead for you before God.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.02,0:08:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.02,0:08:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,when you are the 1st,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.02,0:08:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you are the 2nd.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.50,0:08:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.50,0:08:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The promise is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.50,0:08:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.50,0:08:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he only asked about Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.50,0:08:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we calibrate the level of Jesus Christ,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.81,0:08:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,we get 1000,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.81,0:08:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the maximum possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.94,0:08:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If we measure Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.94,0:08:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So those who believe in Krishna, then Krishna says those who believe in me belong to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.40,0:09:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha says you're on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.70,0:09:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha says you're on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.75,0:09:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So the meaning of yuna is that if you were a little bit foolish in this life, then you can do well in the next life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.75,0:09:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My question is about on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.07,0:09:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You said you're on your own every moment, but it doesn't feel like you've grown up in a Buddhist family.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.63,0:10:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you say that by realizing the pain that occurs every moment, you're letting go of that pain?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.91,0:10:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that we need to surrender to God every instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.04,0:10:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And I grew up in Buddhist family and this teaching doesn't jive well with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.34,0:10:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And then can I understand that dedication as meaning that when every feeling of pain,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.80,0:10:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,when every feeling of pain as they arises, I should, by recognizing it, I surrender it to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.80,0:10:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the same? Am I understanding it correctly?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.95,0:11:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You surrender everything to God all the time, including feelings and occurrences and thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.79,0:11:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.72,0:11:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You surrender everything to God continuously as it arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.72,0:11:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I clearly being aware of it? Is that the act of surrendering?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.30,0:11:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to think back years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.26,0:11:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,As a thing arises, you surrender it to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.10,0:11:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You let go wanting to control it or change it or make it different or squeeze it for some profit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.84,0:11:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It just is as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.47,0:11:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever happens, whatever it is, surrender it to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.47,0:12:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't try to gain any profit from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.47,0:12:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender everything to God voluntarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.62,0:12:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That was Dr. Hopkins' experience in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.62,0:12:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That is sort of like a practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.55,0:12:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, there's nothing to surrender to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.55,0:12:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything just is as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.55,0:12:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the birds flying along.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.55,0:12:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And you let the bird be. You let all of life be like the bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.65,0:12:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice interpreter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.65,0:12:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice table.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.65,0:12:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Wonderful wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.65,0:12:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice water.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.65,0:12:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Good soda.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.65,0:12:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice Kleenex.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.65,0:13:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything just is as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.03,0:13:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't involve you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.03,0:13:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The phenomena are all occurring of their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.03,0:13:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All is occurring of its own nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.03,0:13:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is happening of its own nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.03,0:13:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Because all that seems to be occurring is only an observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.55,0:13:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And creation is continuous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.03,0:13:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Creation is constantly unfolding.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.10,0:13:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And you witness the unfolding of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.10,0:13:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.10,0:13:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.10,0:13:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.10,0:13:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.10,0:13:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.10,0:13:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.10,0:14:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't have to get involved in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.10,0:14:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If it rains, it rains, if it shines, it shines.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.10,0:14:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.10,0:14:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a nice rainy day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.20,0:14:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a nice sunny day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.28,0:14:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a nice warm day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.28,0:14:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's a nice cool day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.28,0:14:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a good day. It's a good day because it's cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.42,0:14:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.80,0:14:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.98,0:14:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That happens of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.77,0:14:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything happens of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.17,0:14:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything happens of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.08,0:14:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In the beginning, you release it, you release it, you release it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.46,0:14:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then after that, it lets go of its own because you don't get attached, so you don't have to let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.10,0:14:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're not attached, you don't have to let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.75,0:14:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You consciously let go of it, but if you keep doing it, you just don't have any obsession with it, so you naturally accept everything as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.34,0:15:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But for me, when I hear the word God, I don't have any special image at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.20,0:15:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When he thinks of God, he cannot conceptualize.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.86,0:15:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No image appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.37,0:15:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.55,0:15:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And to what is surrendering?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.96,0:15:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're looking at, what you're looking at is God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.66,0:15:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.83,0:15:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This is God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.49,0:15:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.87,0:15:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.52,0:15:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is the expression of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.16,0:15:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the sacredness of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.30,0:15:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The sacredness of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.50,0:15:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The sacredness of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.59,0:15:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The sacredness of this table.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.14,0:16:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This is God's expression as a table.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.09,0:16:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,God's expression is Kleenex.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.75,0:16:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,God's expression is water.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.17,0:16:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.20,0:16:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an expression of the sacredness as a table, and the sacredness as a Kleenex.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.08,0:16:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is the sacredness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.37,0:16:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,With an enlightened state, the divinity of everything shines forth
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.44,0:16:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,with complete beauty and holiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.15,0:16:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Beauty and perfection, everything is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.89,0:16:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing you have to do or fix, and with that realization, you see the beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.24,0:17:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.08,0:17:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the beauty of all that exists, beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.66,0:17:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Charm, the charm of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.86,0:17:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.18,0:17:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Next question.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.18,0:17:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the one with hearing disability.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.50,0:17:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And he has a hearing disability.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.00,0:17:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,His question is, he's asking you to pray for his mother, who died of cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.26,0:17:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I understand quite recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.08,0:17:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you pray for his mother, deceased mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.13,0:17:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should I do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.75,0:17:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.75,0:18:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,God doesn't like her, or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.64,0:18:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He just wanted to get more of a blessing, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.11,0:18:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, oh, oh, I see, oh yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.11,0:18:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Does anyone have sign language?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.11,0:18:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Did she have a name?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.11,0:18:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Did she have a name?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.11,0:18:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Who did you pray for?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.69,0:18:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you pray for your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.91,0:18:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.91,0:18:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.97,0:18:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Name, name.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.97,0:18:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Kim Gyeong Nam.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.02,0:18:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Kim Gyeong Nam.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.17,0:18:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.17,0:18:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother's soul is okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.78,0:18:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,His mother's soul is okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.66,0:18:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He says his mother's soul is okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.81,0:18:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.01,0:18:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He says you don't have to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.90,0:19:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The question is, would a writer's way be fit for my job?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.24,0:19:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's suitable, a documentary or a simple literature.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.61,0:19:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.57,0:19:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She's asking whether becoming a professional writer is appropriate for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.57,0:19:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, she works for a TV station as a writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.22,0:19:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And then she's asking whether that job, that vocation is good for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.70,0:19:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, for documentary or for pure literature.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.81,0:19:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Mundane question.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.22,0:19:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Why the question?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.53,0:19:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,She wants to be a good writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.82,0:19:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Good writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.63,0:19:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Good writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.73,0:20:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And also she's asking for your advice to be a good writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.39,0:20:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,To be a good writer?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.07,0:20:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.49,0:20:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask about this lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.57,0:20:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,She has the talent to be a good writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.98,0:20:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.90,0:20:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see, writing, you become energized by what they call the muse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.94,0:20:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,M-U-S-E in English.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.75,0:20:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Muse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.15,0:20:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The muse is like inspiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.53,0:20:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.09,0:20:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when my muse is present, I feel energized and interested in writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.72,0:20:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I get up at 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.75,0:20:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Or 4 o'clock in the morning and start to write, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.49,0:20:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I get up 3 or 4 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.52,0:20:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to jump out of bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.23,0:20:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait to write.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.21,0:21:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,To be a good writer, you need inspiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.44,0:21:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We usually say that inspiration is what we feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.61,0:21:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You need inspiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.96,0:21:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In the case of Dr. Hawkins, if you have that inspiration, you can wake up at 3 o'clock in the morning and write.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.16,0:21:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for some years, I wrote books.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.20,0:21:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the muse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.72,0:21:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,was initiating the desire to write.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.90,0:21:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But now my views is quiet, thank goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.92,0:21:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I wrote eight or nine books, nine stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.55,0:21:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Eight books, or nine books, I don't know what.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.40,0:22:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, now maybe I'm thinking about writing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.25,0:22:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,another little book, commentaries, thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.50,0:22:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and commentaries about things, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.03,0:22:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But not a big book like before, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.94,0:22:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, follow your muse.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.13,0:22:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So don't, don't try and make yourself right
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.43,0:22:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when you don't feel the incentive, the energy, the desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.42,0:22:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that in Korean?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.33,0:22:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Muse?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.44,0:22:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Muuu sse.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.79,0:22:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that a familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.94,0:23:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,No, actually we say feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.51,0:23:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You get a feel first up.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.94,0:23:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.03,0:23:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in English it's almost like, almost like a fantasy that you're muse.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.28,0:23:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I must write.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.28,0:23:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I must dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.28,0:23:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I must sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.30,0:23:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I must be an actor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.76,0:23:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspires you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.76,0:23:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspires you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.41,0:23:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.91,0:23:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a student who is studying psychoanalysis?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.27,0:23:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Psychology.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.27,0:23:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Psychology. And then his question is, what is the meaning that dreams can provide?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.50,0:23:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.50,0:23:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Provide to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.50,0:24:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we can analyze dreams and apply their values to our life, what are the methods of doing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.86,0:24:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, dreams are very important in psychoanalysis. Psychoanalysis, either Freudian, Jungian, there are others too,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.88,0:24:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but Freud and Jung are the two main types of interpretations.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.00,0:24:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And a great deal is learned from the unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.86,0:24:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Because without psychoanalysis, a person is not familiar with their unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.50,0:24:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And in psychoanalysis, the unconscious becomes more into awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.65,0:25:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's very, very useful. And it's very, very true.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.74,0:25:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Dreams are very important in psychology.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.75,0:25:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to understand that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.75,0:25:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud and Jung are the two main scholars.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.75,0:25:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can learn a lot from the unconscious in psychology,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.75,0:25:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but through psychoanalysis, we can learn a lot from the unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.75,0:25:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And what we learn from that is very accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.75,0:25:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He says it's close to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.75,0:25:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in psychoanalysis for, I don't know, five, six years, a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.25,0:25:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day of the week, you go and lay on the couch.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.05,0:25:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And talk about what goes through your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.54,0:25:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And all the things that are repressed out of awareness now come up in awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.56,0:26:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,My psychoanalysis was Freud.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.18,0:26:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,My psychoanalyst was Professor at Columbia University.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.10,0:26:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,His psychoanalyst was psychoanalyzed by Freud.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.61,0:26:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So Freud is like my psychoanalytic grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.13,0:26:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So Freud is like my psychoanalytic grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.13,0:26:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So Freud is like my psychoanalytic grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.42,0:26:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Hawkins, you went to bed at least once a week before a certain period of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.42,0:26:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and after you lay on the couch, you raised your consciousness to the level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.42,0:26:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and you raised your consciousness to the level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.42,0:26:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and the person who did that for Professor Hawkins was a professor at Columbia University,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.42,0:26:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and the professor who taught him was Freud.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.42,0:26:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wanted to talk about Freud to Professor Hawkins
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.42,0:26:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,because he was the grand-grandfather of the psychological analysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.42,0:27:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, through psychoanalysis you understand the things that go on in the world to a greater degree.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.85,0:27:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,With database analysis we begin to understand the things that are going on in the world to a greater degree.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.90,0:27:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud said that in the unconscious, there is eros and also thanatos.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.56,0:27:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,One is the attraction to life and the other is the attraction to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.49,0:28:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,These two things he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.35,0:28:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You see every day in the news somewhere there is a riot with people killing other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.11,0:28:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.11,0:28:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.85,0:28:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is it this morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.85,0:28:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They are killing some, oh, today it's Greece.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.90,0:28:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day they're killing somebody someplace, and the people can't wait for the killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.24,0:28:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,People rush to the killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.11,0:28:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They just can't wait to get shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.35,0:28:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Rush to your death, attracted to the death.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.81,0:28:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a death instinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.18,0:28:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw it, I first saw it in a dog pack.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.68,0:28:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I had my chickens out in the yard with the fence around, and three dogs came into the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.76,0:28:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,yard and they began attacking the chickens.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.48,0:29:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They would kill this chicken, then they would kill this chicken, then they would kill this
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.72,0:29:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,chicken.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.72,0:29:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They just were on a killing bloodlust to kill, kill, kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.72,0:29:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.72,0:29:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.31,0:29:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.72,0:29:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.72,0:29:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.72,0:29:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.72,0:29:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.72,0:30:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.22,0:30:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And in today's world, like, Islamics blow up a whole busload of children, 34 children,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.19,0:30:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and they blow it up, kill all 34 children.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.16,0:30:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you explain such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.64,0:30:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Freud says that's the thanatos in the unconscious and they just invent the religion
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.38,0:30:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to give it a freedom of expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.47,0:30:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.47,0:31:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see it in the teenage killers.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.47,0:31:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In the United States, periodically, some teenage gets a gun and goes into his school
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.81,0:31:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,room and shoots all his classmates.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.81,0:31:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he commits suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.14,0:31:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how can you explain it?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.88,0:31:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't explain it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.88,0:31:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.88,0:31:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,With intelligence or logic or rationality, you can only explain it with Freud's theory of Thanatos.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.08,0:31:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no other explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.65,0:31:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This cannot be explained by intelligence or logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.99,0:32:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only be explained by Freud's idea of Thanatos, which is attracted to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.43,0:32:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only be explained by that instinct, which is attracted to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.51,0:32:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we have some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.18,0:32:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, I would like to know if there is a daily method that ordinary people can use to grow up with this dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.75,0:32:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Dreams, just from intuitive, you can trust your intuition to look at your intuition to what this could be referring to.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.14,0:33:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So the dream might say to you, really, to look at this area, look at this area of your life and see what are your various motives.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.44,0:33:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Examine it, pay attention to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.09,0:33:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So the dream might serve a purpose that you pay attention to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.38,0:33:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.85,0:33:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to do that, but if you make a suggestion, you can use your intuition to look at your dream and see what part of your life you want to observe in your dream, so you can dream and use your intuition to observe the things that you are missing in your life, as an opportunity to observe them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.65,0:33:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,With, I guess, spiritual progression, what I'm thinking of is do the spiritual progression.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.49,0:33:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, with spiritual progression, eventually...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.30,0:33:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,As you get more and more enlightened, you hit a point where the dreams stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.51,0:33:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I never dream anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.83,0:33:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I never dream anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.50,0:34:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It might be because you don't need to repress anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.09,0:34:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, could be so.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.61,0:34:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.51,0:34:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.03,0:34:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The teachings that we hear from you, could they be used to help us to move beyond the level 700?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.61,0:34:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,As work as a karma, they could help us go beyond the level 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.26,0:34:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to worry about going...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.17,0:34:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.01,0:34:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to worry about going to level 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.88,0:35:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You start the spiritual process, and then it goes where it goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.78,0:35:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't try and control.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.55,0:35:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no particular goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.07,0:35:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The person overall says, I want to become enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.03,0:35:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.36,0:35:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's a certain orientation.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.69,0:35:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And wherever you are in the process is okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.88,0:35:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If you start spiritual work, don't try to control it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.88,0:35:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.92,0:35:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Wherever you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.19,0:35:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.30,0:35:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Wherever you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.92,0:35:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the state comes on spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.26,0:35:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That state of consciousness occurs spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.86,0:36:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What's important is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.92,0:36:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The important thing is to be oriented in that direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.25,0:36:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,As a life goal to become enlightened appeals to 1 in 10 million people on the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.50,0:36:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The desire to become enlightened, making that your prime goal in life,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.28,0:36:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,only 1 in 10 million people on the street, 1 in 10 million has that orientation.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.65,0:37:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one reason it's rare. It's few people choose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.94,0:37:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha said,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.94,0:37:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Fortunate is to be born a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.86,0:37:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,More fortunate than that is to be born a human and then to hear of enlightenment, to hear of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.92,0:37:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Rarer still is to hear of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.92,0:37:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And then pursue it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.78,0:38:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So we give thanks for the Buddha, for the message.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.40,0:38:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when we worship the Buddha, we pick up that energy that drives you through to the state of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.32,0:38:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we revere the Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.67,0:38:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jesus Christ taught salvation. The Buddha taught enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.98,0:38:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ taught salvation. The Buddha taught enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.30,0:38:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ taught salvation. The Buddha taught enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.76,0:38:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a different question.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.76,0:38:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,10 years ago, the dark side of the inner world began to be seen and it has become more and more severe.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.76,0:38:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It is very painful because of this. How should we deal with these parts?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.76,0:39:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,About 10, since about 10 years ago, some dark spots within me, some dark side inside was spotted.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.76,0:39:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Dark side was what?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.01,0:39:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Was witnessed, was noticed by me.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.01,0:39:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, he noticed. He noticed the dark spot in himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.01,0:39:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The dark spot in himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.01,0:39:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.01,0:39:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's getting severe and severe. And I've been sort of agonizing about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.01,0:39:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's getting worse?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.01,0:39:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's getting worse and worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.01,0:39:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What does he mean? Evil? Hate? What does he mean by dark spot?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.01,0:39:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.01,0:39:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.01,0:39:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The emotions and thoughts below 200. He's experiencing those emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.01,0:39:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.01,0:39:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And he wants to overcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.01,0:39:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.01,0:40:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you lead a spiritual life, to overcome them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.44,0:40:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it takes years for them to rise up and you stop repressing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.98,0:40:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You start to accept them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.98,0:40:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,First, you accept the things you don't like.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.78,0:40:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate people.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.78,0:40:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate people.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.78,0:40:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate people.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.61,0:40:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.61,0:40:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.61,0:40:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.61,0:40:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you want to kill people. So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.03,0:40:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They have to be the way I want them to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.03,0:40:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So I want to control them, make them different.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.03,0:40:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.03,0:41:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,After a while, you say, I don't want to make them different.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.03,0:41:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They can be how they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.21,0:41:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you say, people can't help being what they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.48,0:41:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you realize that people can't change their own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.88,0:41:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't change that easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.88,0:41:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I admit.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.88,0:41:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You take a religious maniac and he wants to blow up a busload of children.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.07,0:41:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He blows up a busload of children.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.51,0:41:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a religious evangelist who tries to blow up a busload of children.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.67,0:41:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,TheIC MADASSAH
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.86,0:41:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He's suffering from—his mind has been indoctrinated to think that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.82,0:42:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So the perpetrator is at the same time the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.75,0:42:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the victim of that kind of thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.75,0:42:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't have to savor growing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.88,0:42:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He has knowledge for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.88,0:42:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,When you take it, can you stand up for yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.88,0:42:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.88,0:42:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Jesus Christ said, there's only one sin, ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.92,0:42:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we forgive people because they don't know any better.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.73,0:42:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of that arises the Buddha's compassion for all things.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.82,0:43:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Compassion for all human beings. Compassion for their limitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.55,0:43:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, acknowledge that you have those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.01,0:43:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not an expression. Acknowledge it and be at ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.03,0:43:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Or do you just need to look at the negative emotions as they pass by?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.03,0:44:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch them subside without acting them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.05,0:44:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He can forgive himself for thinking those thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.05,0:44:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He has to forgive himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.46,0:44:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,See, when you start looking at the unconscious, you have to accept what comes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.13,0:44:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What comes up is usually...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.13,0:44:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,...not so pleasant.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.13,0:44:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, you wouldn't have repressed it into your unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.36,0:44:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When you check your consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.42,0:44:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,first, acknowledge the negative emotions that come up.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.42,0:44:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if they weren't so negative,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.42,0:44:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,they wouldn't have been suppressed unconsciously.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.42,0:44:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you raise your consciousness to those things,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.42,0:45:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,even if they're negative, it's important to acknowledge them at ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.28,0:45:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When you find the way to your heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.28,0:45:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,with the help of your teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.28,0:45:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you are studying to meet the true self through the inner conversation with the God of the nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.28,0:45:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you give me some advice?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.28,0:45:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you explain about the consciousness of the nature before the Creator?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.71,0:45:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,By seeking the way through heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.86,0:45:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,she met a teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.86,0:45:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,By seeking what?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.86,0:45:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The way through heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.86,0:45:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The way through the heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.86,0:45:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.86,0:45:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The way through love, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.86,0:45:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.86,0:45:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, he met a teacher who taught her that to meet your true self,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.23,0:45:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to have inner conversation with God.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.23,0:46:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,She's doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.86,0:46:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.86,0:46:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there good advice?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.86,0:46:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.86,0:46:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,One more question.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.86,0:46:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This teacher is talking about some original consciousness prior to the Creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.50,0:46:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.13,0:46:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Some original consciousness prior?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.13,0:46:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Prior to Creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.13,0:46:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Prior to the Creator?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.13,0:46:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, prior to the Creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.55,0:46:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Makes no sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.76,0:46:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't understand. How?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.76,0:46:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean thoughts created God?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.17,0:46:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the question?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.17,0:46:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but he's giving explanations.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.17,0:46:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Her teacher is giving explanations about some original consciousness prior to the Creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.30,0:46:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, oh, oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.30,0:46:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And she's doubting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.30,0:46:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether that is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.44,0:46:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.44,0:46:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,My understanding of it is the same as pretty much revealed in Scripture.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.17,0:47:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In the beginning was the Godhead.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.59,0:47:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The beginning was the Godhead.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.40,0:47:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The Godhead.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.40,0:47:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of which arose God.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.67,0:47:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of which arose creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.67,0:47:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The first emanation from God was light, is symbolized as light.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.32,0:47:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the Godhead arose consciousness as light.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.63,0:47:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the light of God arose consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.63,0:48:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of consciousness arose the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.98,0:48:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.46,0:48:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.46,0:48:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.46,0:48:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the consciousness arose the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.46,0:48:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And the universe was created to be evolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.28,0:48:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's evolutionary by nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.61,0:48:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The universe was created to evolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.96,0:48:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It was created to evolve in its essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.17,0:48:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So evolution is continuous and ongoing and eternal.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.44,0:48:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why evolution is continuous and eternal.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.44,0:49:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It is measured by facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.30,0:49:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.30,0:49:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have any advice that she's seeking to meet her true self through inner conversations
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.30,0:49:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,with God?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.30,0:49:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one style.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.30,0:49:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.13,0:49:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one style.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.13,0:49:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.13,0:49:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one style.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.13,0:49:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like divinity seeking to recognize its own divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.13,0:49:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a paradox.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.71,0:49:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Like divinity seeking to recognize its own divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.21,0:49:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a paradox that she brought.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.21,0:49:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That it was brought up.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.21,0:49:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.21,0:49:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.21,0:49:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.21,0:49:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.13,0:49:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.13,0:49:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.13,0:49:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.13,0:49:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.42,0:49:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.42,0:49:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.42,0:49:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.42,0:49:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.48,0:49:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.48,0:49:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.48,0:49:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.48,0:49:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.48,0:49:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.48,0:49:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.19,0:49:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.19,0:49:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.19,0:49:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.19,0:49:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.19,0:50:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.19,0:50:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.19,0:50:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.88,0:50:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.55,0:50:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.55,0:50:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.55,0:50:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
